title: Samsung Refrigerator new model not making ice

full_content.content: Samsung Refrigerator new model not making ice
Common reasons your Samsung Refrigerator new model not making ice
The most common reasons your Samsung refrigerator new model is not making ice are a faulty icemaker assembly, a clogged icemaker fill tube, or a malfunctioning PCB.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over 20,000 Samsung refrigerators. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Samsung refrigerator

A faulty icemaker could be the reason your refrigerator is not making ice. The icemaker unit is responsible for collecting water, freezing it into cubes, and dispensing the ice into the storage bin. If the icemaker is malfunctioning, it may not complete these tasks correctly, resulting in no ice production. You might notice the ice tray remains empty, or the icemaker doesn't cycle properly. To address this issue, check the icemaker for any visible signs of damage or malfunction. If you suspect the icemaker is faulty, schedule an in-home repair appointment through Sears Home Services to have a technician inspect and replace the icemaker, ensuring your refrigerator produces ice as it should.
How to replace an icemaker assembly

A clogged or frozen icemaker fill tube could be the reason your new model refrigerator is not making ice. The fill tube supplies water to the icemaker, allowing it to produce ice. If this tube becomes blocked or frozen, it prevents water from reaching the icemaker, stopping ice production altogether. You may notice the ice tray remains empty or ice cubes are unusually small. To resolve this issue, inspect the fill tube for any blockages or ice buildup and clear it accordingly. If the problem persists, schedule an in-home repair appointment through Sears Home Services to have a technician inspect and clear the fill tube, ensuring your icemaker functions properly.
Why won't my refrigerator make ice?

A malfunctioning printed circuit board (PCB) could be the reason your new refrigerator is not making ice. The PCB controls the various functions of the icemaker, including water supply and freezing cycles. If the PCB is faulty, it may not send the correct signals to the icemaker, disrupting the ice production process. You might notice that the icemaker isn't cycling properly or that no ice is being produced at all. To address this issue, inspect the PCB for any visible damage or signs of failure. If you suspect the PCB is the problem, schedule an in-home repair appointment through Sears Home Services to have a technician diagnose and replace the faulty PCB, ensuring your icemaker resumes proper operation. A failing board may cause a chattering or clicking noise from the refrigerator and may emit a burning odor. Due to the potential impact on multiple components, it is advisable to have a Sears Home Services professional conduct diagnostic tests on the board to confirm if replacement is necessary.
How to replace the electronic control board in a refrigerator
Why is my brand new Samsung fridge not making ice?

When you have just installed your Samsung refrigerator it will take 6 to 12 hours for the refrigerator to produce ice. The ice maker should then begin dumping ice every 30 minutes until the ice bin is full.
If it has been more than 12 hours since your installed your Samsung fridge, follow these troubleshooting steps to get your ice maker working.

Your Samsung refrigerator’s use and care guide will often indicate that you’ll need to wait a day or two for your ice maker to begin producing ice even though the process will often begin within 12 hours after installing the fridge.
Make sure that you have the freezer temperature set properly at 0 degrees.
Check the ice maker setting to make sure that it’s turned on. The instructions for turning on the ice maker for many common Samsung refrigerator models are shown in the image below.
When your ice maker isn’t working in a brand new Samsung refrigerator, try resetting the control boards in the refrigerator.
Unplug the refrigerator or shut off the house circuit breaker to completely disconnect electrical power.
Wait 2 minutes to allow the control boards to reset.
Plug the refrigerator power cord back in or reset the house circuit breaker to restore power to the refrigerator.
The control boards in your Samsung refrigerator will reboot and reset. The ice maker may then begin working.

If resetting the control board doesn’t help, check for water dispensing properly through the water dispenser. If water isn’t dispensing properly, check the water filter to make sure that it’s installed properly.
Here’s a video that shows how to properly install the water filter in a common Samsung refrigerator:
If the refrigerator water filter is installed properly, check the water supply going to the fridge.
Make sure that the water supply cut-off valve is turned on. Turn that valve on if you find it shut off.
Check for a kink in the water supply line. Reposition the water line so that it isn’t kinked if necessary.

Shut off the water supply cut-off valve and disconnect the water line from the back of your Samsung fridge. Place the end of the water line in a bucket and briefly open the water supply cut-off valve to check for water flow from the end of water line. If you don’t see water flowing from the water supply line, have a plumber fix the water supply going to your refrigerator.
If all of these tips don’t help you get ice from your Samsung refrigerator ice maker, you’ll need to call Samsung to get additional help or have the new refrigerator repaired under the warranty.
What to expect when you experience a Samsung refrigerator new model not making ice issue
How is the refrigerator new model not making ice issue fixed?

Correcting most refrigerator new not making ice issues involves replacing the icemaker assembly, icemaker fill tube, or the PCB. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a refrigerator new model not making ice problem

When a refrigerator is not making ice, it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts, we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of refrigerator failures.
What to look out for with a refrigerator new not making ice diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your refrigerator problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why is my new Samsung refrigerator not making ice?

A new Samsung refrigerator may fail to make ice if the ice maker is turned off, the water filter is clogged, or the ice maker assembly is defective. Ensuring proper water flow and regularly replacing the water filter often solves the issue.
How do I fix a Samsung refrigerator that isn’t making ice?

Check that the ice maker is switched on, replace the water filter if it’s past its lifespan, and ensure the ice bin is properly seated. If these steps don’t resolve the issue, schedule a professional inspection.
What causes ice production to stop in a new Samsung fridge?
Clogged filters, misaligned ice bins, or restricted water lines can lead to ice production problems. Resetting the ice maker module may help if the unit has experienced a minor glitch.
Can a newly installed fridge need time before making ice?

Yes, new Samsung refrigerators often need several hours—sometimes up to 24 hours—before they start producing ice. Make sure the water supply is properly connected and the freezer is at the correct temperature.

full_content.content: How Does a Refrigerator Ice Maker Work?
Learn how a refrigerator ice maker works and how to keep it in top shape.

A compressor is a mechanical device that increases the pressure of a gas by reducing its volume, essential in various systems including refrigerators, air conditioners, and HVAC units for cooling and refrigeration processes.
A condenser is a component of HVAC and refrigeration systems, responsible for releasing absorbed heat from the refrigerant into the outside air or a water line, thus facilitating the cooling process.
What is a Dual Ice Maker?

A dual ice maker is a feature in some refrigerators that includes two separate ice makers: one in the fridge compartment and another in the freezer section. This setup doubles the appliance's ice-making capacity.

A French-door refrigerator features two doors that open side-by-side on the top section for the refrigerator compartment, with a bottom freezer drawer, combining style, efficiency, and easy access to both refrigerated and frozen goods.
